- target
    - find a SHA1 collision pair to send to remote host
    - username != password
    - sha1(username) == sha1(password)
- answer
    - using google's SHA1's collision pdf file
        - shattered-1.pdf
        - shattered-2.pdf
    - then use base 64 to encode
        - in Centos, using "-w 0" to disable line wrapper
            - cat shattered-1.pdf | base64 -w 0 > shattered-1-base64.pdf
            - cat shattered-2.pdf | base64 -w 0 > shattered-2-base64.pdf
    - then send to remote
- refs
    - https://shattered.io/
    - https://bamboofox.cs.nctu.edu.tw/courses/4/challenges/84
